  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q104.a002.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">s object. For while subjects have many obligations towards their superiors, this one, that they are bound to obey their commands, stands out as special among the rest. Wherefore obedience is a special virtue , and its specific object is a command tacit or express, because the superior's</data>
  <data key="d18"></data>
  <data key="d19">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
