  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">is the will , in so far as, by his will, man makes use of all other goods. Therefore, properly speaking, the virtue of obedience, whereby we contemn our own will for God's sake, is more praiseworthy than the other moral virtues , which contemn other goods for the sake of God . Hence Greg</data>
