  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q104.a006.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">Faith in Christ is the origin and cause of justice , according to Romans 3:22 , "The justice of God by faith of Jesus Christ :" wherefore faith in Christ does not void the order of justice , but strengthens it." Now the order of justice requires that subjects</data>
  <data key="d18"></data>
  <data key="d19">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
<edge source="st.ii-ii.q104.a006" target="concept.superior_role" id="edge.st.ii-ii.q104.a006.treated_in.concept.superior_role">
  <data key="d6">edge.st.ii-ii.q104.a006.treated_in.concept.superior_role</data>
  <data key="d7">st.ii-ii.q104.a006</data>
  <data key="d8">II-II q.104 a.6 — Are the faithful bound to obey the secular power?</data>
  <data key="d9">article</data>
  <data key="d10">treated_in</data>
  <data key="d11">concept.superior_role</data>
  <data key="d12">Superior Role</data>
  <data key="d13">role</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.st-ii-ii-q104-a006-treated-in-concept-superior-role-st-ii-ii-q104-a006-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q104.a006.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">st does not void the order of justice , but strengthens it." Now the order of justice requires that subjects obey their superiors, else the stability of human affairs would cease. Hence faith in Christ does not excuse the faithful from the obligation of obeying secular princes.</data>
  <data key="d18"></data>
  <data key="d19">reviewed_structural_editorial</data>
</edge>
