  <data key="d16">structural_editorial</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:24:12 ; I-II:72:5 ; I-II:88:1 ), a mortal sin is one that is contrary to charity which is the cause of spiritual life. Now by charity we love God and our neighbor. The charity of God requires that we obey His commandments, as stated abo</data>
