  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">irtue : thus illiberality is more opposed to liberality than prodigality is. Now a vice may be opposed to the virtue of gratitude by way of excess, for instance if one were to show gratitude for things for which gratitude is not due, or sooner than it is due, as stated above ( II-II:106:4</data>
