  <data key="d17">atitude, because the virtue of gratitude, as stated above ( II-II:106:6 ), inclines to return something more. Wherefore ingratitude is properly denominated from being a deficiency of gratitude. Now every deficiency or privation takes its species from the opposite habit : for blindness and d</data>
